  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n## 2026-05-02 22:15 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 2] The current PM price band is still the right cut; don't overfit the low-fill tail\n\n**Task:** Retest the live PM smart-entry price band against realized `confidence_outcomes.jsonl` rows and decide whether `min_price=0.50` / `max_price=0.525` needs a change before the next weekday session.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- Rotation pointed to **P2**.\n- Current live config confirmed in `trading_bot.py`: `min_price=0.50`, `max_price=0.525`, `max_bias=70`, active hours **[11,12,20]**, and V5a pass means `abs(bias_score) >= 45`.\n- Execution detail matters: the filter caps `target_price`, then order placement allows `target_price * 1.02`, so `max_price=0.525` permits normal fills up to about **0.5355**.\n- In 201 realized outcome rows, active hours **[11,12,20]** are **30 trades, 70.0% WR, +0.353 avg pnl_pct**.\n- Active-hour + `v5a_pass=true` is **17 trades, 70.6% WR, +0.364 avg pnl_pct**.\n- Active + V5a + current target band (`0.50 <= target <= 0.525`, fill <= ~0.5355) is **15 trades, 80.0% WR, +0.546 avg pnl_pct, +8.19 sum pnl_pct**.\n- Active + V5a + high tail **>=0.5355** is only **3 trades, 33.3% WR, -0.378 avg**, and the truly high fills above **0.5355** are **0/2**. The current cap already removes that danger zone.\n- Price-bin read inside active + V5a rows:\n  - **0.4950-0.5049:** 2 trades, 50.0% WR, -0.010 avg \u2014 too thin / not compelling\n  - **0.5050-0.5151:** 8 trades, 87.5% WR, +0.704 avg \u2014 core sweet spot\n  - **0.5152-0.5253:** 4 trades, 75.0% WR, +0.428 avg \u2014 still good\n  - **0.5254-0.5355:** 1 trade, 100% WR, +0.867 avg \u2014 single winner, allowed by live slippage cap\n  - **0.5356+:** 2 trades, 0.0% WR, -1.000 avg \u2014 toxic high-price tail\n- By hour on active + V5a rows: **11h 57.1% WR**, **12h 87.5% WR**, **20h 50.0% WR on n=2**.\n- I wrote the artifact to `/home/ubuntu/clawd/research/p2-current-price-band-validation-2026-05-02-2215.md`.\n\n**My thinking:** The band is earning its keep. The real profit center is not blindly cheap entries; it is the 0.505-0.5253 zone where payout is still good but the PM quote is not dead/no-edge. Raising the lower bound off two low-fill rows would be overfitting, especially because live filtering uses the PM target quote, not the final fill. The high tail is the clearer enemy, and the existing cap already handles it.\n\n**Decision:** Make **no code/config change**. Keep `min_price=0.50`, `max_price=0.525`, active hours **[11,12,20]**, and keep **20 UTC** on probation rather than cutting it on n=2.\n\n**Next:** On the next Pillar 2 pass, join price-band buckets to **fast regime** and **transition_context.posture**. If near-50 fills only lose during `risk_rising` / `HIGH_VOL`, ship a regime-conditioned price filter instead of a blunt price-floor raise.\n\n## 2026-05-02 22:07 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 1] BTC copy-intel just got much cleaner because the last meaningful bear exited\n\n**Task:**",
